      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Venomous Bite (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Swarmer lunges forward, attempting to bite a target with its multitude of stingers and fangs. It makes a melee attack, dealing D4+1 Poison damage on a hit.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Acid Spray (Magical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Swarmer releases a spray of corrosive acid in front of it. Creatures within the cone must succeed on a Dodge check or take D6 Acid damage and have their Armor reduced by 1 until they can repair it back at Camp.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Swarm Assault",
        "description": "<div><p>The Swarmer engulfs a target within its monstrous swarm, attacking from multiple angles and dealing 2 Piercing damage. The target must succeed on an Endurance check or be Blinded until their next turn as the swarm obscures their vision.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>Swarmers are horrifying and relentless monsters, a nightmarish amalgamation born from the union of thousands of smaller creatures. Their colossal form is a grotesque mass of chittering insects, squirming worms, and writhing serpents, all fused together in a monstrous swarm. Swarmers attack with unrelenting ferocity, unleashing a deluge of venomous bites, stings, and corrosive secretions upon their prey. Their origin is a complete mystery, but as most things in Ker Nethalas, it's most likely yet another Vaelorian aberration.</p></div>",
